## 7. Important Considerations

### Security
- Hash passwords with bcrypt
- Implement rate limiting on APIs
- Validate all user inputs
- Use HTTPS everywhere
- Store sensitive data encrypted
- Implement CSRF protection

### Performance
- Use database indexing (especially for location queries)
- Implement caching (Redis)
- Optimize image uploads (compression, CDN)
- Use pagination for list endpoints
- Implement database query optimization

### Scalability
- Use message queues for heavy operations (Bull, RabbitMQ)
- Implement load balancing
- Use microservices architecture for large scale
- Database sharding for massive data

### Compliance
- GDPR compliance for user data
- PCI DSS for payment processing
- Terms of Service and Privacy Policy
- Local transportation regulations
- Insurance compliance

